author: rhuijben
msg: Perform another round of code cleanup in the libsvn_client external handling.
Extract the export code and pass the defining abspath around for old externals
instead of the more expensive to get old url (which isn't used yet anyway).
* subversion/libsvn_client/externals.c
(external_change_baton_t): Remove two variables.
(handle_external_item_removal): Replace old_url and wri_abspath arguments
with a defining abspath argument that can be used to retrieve the
information.
(handle_external_item_change): Update argument. Remove comment describing why
we shouldn't do something. Remove export code that didn't need the
information whether an external was a file external anyway.
(handle_externals_change): Forward argument renaming.
(svn_client__handle_externals): Use information from the hash instead of
retrieving it again via the key.
(svn_client__export_externals): Export directly instead of using a helper
function.
